OL,3,CThe trailblazing trans woman who made
OL,4,CWales her home after being outed
OL,6,FAfter returning home from the Merchant
OL,7,FNavy, April attempted suicide, which
OL,8,Fled her to be sent to a mental
OL,9,Finstitution for electric shock
OL,10,Ftreatment.
OL,12,FIn May of 1960 April became part of
OL,13,FLGBTQ+ history. For the first time in
OL,14,Fher life, April woke up as a woman.
OL,16,FAt the age of 25, she became one of
OL,17,Fthe first people to undergo successful
OL,18,Fgender reassignment surgery.
