OL,3,CThe trailblazing trans woman who made
OL,4,CWales her home after being outed
OL,6,FFrom that point, April was a regular
OL,7,Ffeature in the tabloids, including
OL,8,Fduring her divorce from her first
OL,9,Fhusband, The Honourable Arthur
OL,10,FCorbett, in 1970.
OL,12,FTheir marriage was ruled to be invalid
OL,13,Fand annulled, on the grounds that
OL,14,FApril remained a biological man,
OL,15,Fsetting a legal precedent that wasn't
OL,16,Foverturned until the 2004 Gender
OL,17,FRecognition Act was passed.
OL,19,FIn an effort to escape the media
OL,20,Fspotlight, April moved to Hay-on-Wye
OL,21,Fin the late 1970s.
